40|$|I wish {{to raise}} two issues {{with respect to}} Professor Koplow 2 ̆ 7 s article. The first is whether it is proper for the American Society of International Law to {{undertake}} the report which served {{as the basis for}} the Koplow piece. I believe that it is improper for the Society to issue a <b>collective</b> public <b>statement</b> endorsing one side of a partisan political controversy. Secondly, with respect to the substance of Koplow 2 ̆ 7 s argument, I disagree with parts of his analysis and find his proposed solution for the dilemma of treaty interpretation unsatisfactory in principle and unworkable in practice...|$|R
